	<tr>
		
			<td colspan="2" bgcolor="#DEDACB" background="http://www.everlore.com/gimages/tb_beige.gif">
		
				<font face="verdana" size="2" color="black">
				To get the hermit out if you do not cast, best place to stand is at the right side of the chimney in back of the house. stand right inside the corner where the chimney meets the house, and when he starts casting his buffs, say &quot;I will kill you&quot;. the hermit will say &quot;so be it&quot; if you are successful. immediately run away from the house and wait for the hermit to come out (he jumps out through the chimney) otherwise you will have to fight him through the walls and may not be able to loot his corpse.<BR>
<BR>
the hermit conned white to me at lvl20, and cons blue from 21 all the way up to lvl28!<BR>
<BR>
he drops the cracked flute and sheet music for the quest, and when he has a weapon, it is Fine Steel (i've gotten short sword, long sword, 2handed sword, and scimitar from him). also, he drops anywhere from 2copper to 3platinum... not to mention the experience is nice =)<BR>
<BR>
unless you cast or have some sort of healing to rely upon, i wouldn't reccomend soloing the hermit until you're into your 20s. at 22, i can defeat him with up to 2bubbles of health left, but that is usually after successfully using my mend skill (monk)... casters solo the hermit best since they have pets to take the damage he doles out (up to 42 per hit against me), and the hermit has very good melee defenses... but then again, if you're in it for experience you're better off running around SK killing anything that cons blue (it'll be faster and hurt less hehe)
				</font>
			</td>

	</tr>
	
